Exercise: `init`
----------------

\begin{code}
{-@ init :: (Int -> a) -> Nat -> List a @-}
init _ 0 = Emp
init f n = f n ::: init f (n-1)
\end{code}

<br>

<div class="fragment">
**Q:** Can you fix the type of `init` so the below is safe?

<br>

\begin{code}
sanDiegoWeather :: Year Int
sanDiegoWeather = Year (init (const 72) 12)
\end{code}
