Exercise: `init'`
------------------

\begin{code}
{-@ init' :: (Int -> a) -> n:Nat -> List a @-}
init' f n = go 0
  where
    go i | i < n     = f i ::: go (i+1)
         | otherwise = Emp
\end{code}

<br>

<div class="fragment">
**Q:** For bonus points, fix `init'` so the below is safe?

<br>

\begin{code}
sanDiegoWeather' :: Year Int
sanDiegoWeather' = Year (init' (const 72) 12)
\end{code}
